import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['net_generation'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of net electricity generation over the years?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.groupby(['source']).sum().reset_index()
    data['proportion'] = data['net_generation'] / data['net_generation'].sum()
    plt.bar(data['source'], data['proportion'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c'])
    plt.title('What is the proportion of electricity generated from each source?')
    plt.ylabel('Proportion')
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylim(0, 1)
    for i, v in enumerate(data['proportion']):
        plt.text(i, v + 0.05, str(round(v, 2)), ha='center')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['net_generation'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net electricity generation?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
